Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, place @butter{2%tablespoons} and a pinch of @Italian Seasoning{pinch}; bring to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

> If you have a toaster oven, feel free to skip preheating.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and dice @sweet potato{1}(peeled and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounces}(large stems removed).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoons} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounces} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

Stir sweet potato, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @Italian Seasoning{1%teaspoon}, water, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} into pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and simmer for ~{7%minutes}.

> Save the rest of the Italian Seasoning for another use.

Once soup has simmered for ~{7%minutes}, uncover pot and stir in kale. Simmer, uncovered, until kale is wilted and sweet potato is tender, ~{5-7%minutes} more. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add another 1/4-1/2 cup water and an extra pinch of salt if you prefer a brothier soup.

Meanwhile, mix softened @butter{2%tablespoons} and @Italian Seasoning{pinch} until thoroughly combined. Season with salt.

> If butter is not yet softened, microwave for 5-10 seconds.

Halve @demi-baguette{1}(halved lengthwise); spread herb butter onto cut sides. Toast, cut sides up, on top rack (or in a #toaster oven{}) until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Halve each baguette piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between bowls and top with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoons}. Serve with toasts on the side.